.TH HUSHWHEEL 1 "March 2026" "hushwheel 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hushwheel \- theatrical dictionary fixture with a giant static glossary table and Doxygen codex
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hushwheel
.I lookup
.I TERM
.br
.B hushwheel
.I prefix
.I PREFIX
.br
.B hushwheel
.I category
.I NAME
.br
.B hushwheel
.I stats
.br
.B hushwheel
.I about
.SH DESCRIPTION
Hushwheel is a deliberately oversized C fixture whose archive now spans a giant coordinator file,
eight spoke sources, and generated Doxygen documentation. Its lore cross-indexes id Software games
and characters, scripture, and legendary software developers inside editorial narrative frames.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B lookup
Print a full glossary entry.
.TP
.B prefix
Print compact rows for every term whose name starts with the given prefix.
.TP
.B category
Print every entry filed under the named category.
.TP
.B stats
Print entry, category, district, and average ember-index counts.
.TP
.B about
Describe the archive.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I src/hushwheel.c
Large coordinator source with the Doxygen mainpage, canonical entries, and CLI dispatch.
.TP
.I src/hushwheel_spoke_*.c
Generated spoke tables that hold the bulk of the glossary entries.
.TP
.I docs/hushwheel-reference.pdf
Generated Doxygen PDF linked from the README and packaged with the fixture.
